---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { SITE } from '../data/site';
import { METRICS } from '../data/claims';
---

<Base title="Update Tracker" description="Corsa Legends Alpha update status — official title changes, 2 cars + new race, and Roblox API snapshot dates.">
  <div class="hero-grid">
    <div>
      <div class="panel hero">
        <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> Update Tracker</span>
        <h1>Update<br/>Tracker</h1>
        <p class="lead">Tracks what is officially confirmed from Roblox API and game title — not third-party speculation.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="panel section" style="margin-top: 16px;">
        <div class="section-head">
          <div>
            <h2>Current official status</h2>
            <p>From Roblox API snapshot {SITE.metricsDate}</p>
          </div>
          <span class="pill">Alpha</span>
        </div>

        <div class="answer-strip" style="margin: 0;">
          <div>
            <strong>[🏎️2 CARS + NEW RACE] Corsa Legends [ALPHA]</strong>
            <span>Official title from Roblox API. Game is actively in Alpha — expect active development and potential instability.</span>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 style="margin: 20px 0 10px; font-size: 16px;">What the official title confirms</h2>

        <div class="update-list">
          <div class="update-item">
            <h3>🏎️ 2 New Cars</h3>
            <p>The official game title lists "2 CARS" as part of the current update. No further car list or names are published here — official API does not provide a named car inventory.</p>
            <div class="update-meta">
              <span class="pill">Confirmed from official title</span>
              <span class="pill" style="color: var(--warn); border-color: var(--warn);">Names not listed</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="update-item">
            <h3>🏁 New Race</h3>
            <p>Official title confirms a new race was added in this update cycle. Specific race routes or details are not published — official API does not confirm route data.</p>
            <div class="update-meta">
              <span class="pill">Confirmed from official title</span>
              <span class="pill" style="color: var(--warn); border-color: var(--warn);">Route not published</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="update-item">
            <h3>🔄 Alpha Status</h3>
            <p>Game is officially marked Alpha on Roblox. This means active development, potential bugs, and possible wipes or changes. Use at your own risk.</p>
            <div class="update-meta">
              <span class="pill">Confirmed from Roblox API</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 style="margin: 24px 0 10px; font-size: 16px;">Game scope from official description</h2>
        <div class="update-list">
          <div class="update-item">
            <h3>80+ Cars and Trims</h3>
            <p>Official Roblox description states "over 80 cars and trims". This is the only official car count available.</p>
            <div class="update-meta">
              <span class="pill">Official description</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="update-item">
            <h3>Customization Features</h3>
            <p>Paint, interior, rims, tint, performance upgrades — all officially mentioned in the Roblox game description.</p>
            <div class="update-meta">
              <span class="pill">Official description</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="update-item">
            <h3>Live Races</h3>
            <p>Official Roblox description confirms live races exist as a game mode.</p>
            <div class="update-meta">
              <span class="pill">Official description</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="can-cannot" style="margin-top: 20px;">
          <div class="can-card">
            <h3>✓ Confirmed</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Alpha status</li>
              <li>2 new cars added</li>
              <li>New race added</li>
              <li>80+ cars/trims scope</li>
              <li>Live races feature</li>
              <li>Customization options</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cannot-card">
            <h3>✗ Not confirmed</h3>
            <ul>
              <li>Specific car names</li>
              <li>Race route or track layouts</li>
              <li>Update patch notes</li>
              <li>Car values or tier list</li>
              <li>Exact tuning numbers</li>
              <li>Best car or engine</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside>
      <div class="panel side">
        <h2>API Snapshot</h2>
        <div class="metric-row" style="margin: 0;">
          <div class="metric-item">
            <strong>{METRICS.visits}</strong>
            <span>Total Visits</span>
          </div>
          <div class="metric-item">
            <strong>{METRICS.favorites}</strong>
            <span>Favorites</span>
          </div>
          <div class="metric-item">
            <strong>{METRICS.playing}</strong>
            <span>Playing Now</span>
          </div>
          <div class="metric-item">
            <strong>{METRICS.upvotes}</strong>
            <span>Upvotes</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="font-size: 11px; color: var(--quiet); margin-top: 10px;">Snapshot date: {METRICS.date}. Metrics change frequently.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="panel side" style="margin-top: 14px;">
        <h2>Next code milestone</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted);">Official description says a new code comes at</p>
        <p style="font-size: 28px; font-weight: 900; color: var(--accent); margin: 8px 0;">{METRICS.date.includes('2026') ? '90,000' : '—'}</p>
        <p style="font-size: 13px; color: var(--muted);">likes goal (from Roblox description). No code is active yet beyond <strong>75K</strong>.</p>
        <a href="/codes/" style="color: var(--accent); font-size: 13px; display:block; margin-top: 10px;">→ Code Status Page</a>
      </div>

      <div class="panel side" style="margin-top: 14px;">
        <h2>How updates are tracked</h2>
        <p style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--muted); line-height: 1.5;">We check the official Roblox API title and description for changes. When the title changes (e.g. "2 CARS + NEW RACE"), we update this tracker.</p>
        <p style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--quiet); margin-top: 8px;"><a href="/sources/" style="color: var(--accent);">→ Source trust info</a></p>
      </div>
    </aside>
  </div>
</Base>
